1
00:01:05,690 --> 00:01:07,150
Seung-hee.

2
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:09,527
Your twin brother is
an SNU law student now.

3
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:10,528
What will you do?

4
00:01:10,612 --> 00:01:12,447
Please.

5
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:15,075
It's enough to have my mom
compare me to Seung-ho.

6
00:01:18,161 --> 00:01:19,829
I'm just wondering,

7
00:01:20,413 --> 00:01:22,040
but where's Ki-young applying?

8
00:01:22,540 --> 00:01:23,541
Ki-young?

9
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:26,753
He's only applying
to schools in Seoul, right?

10
00:01:26,836 --> 00:01:28,129
Yes.

11
00:01:29,798 --> 00:01:31,424
So he's going to Seoul after all.

12
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:35,220
Why do you suddenly look so down?

13
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:37,222
Are you interested in him?

14
00:01:37,806 --> 00:01:38,890
No.

15
00:01:38,973 --> 00:01:39,849
No way.

16
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,602
No one in our class likes him.

17
00:01:43,436 --> 00:01:44,395
Right, Jae-eun?

18
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:47,482
Yes, right.

19
00:01:48,024 --> 00:01:48,858
That's odd.

20
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:50,443
You sit next to him, don't you?

21
00:01:51,027 --> 00:01:53,321
-Yes.
-Isn't he so gentle and kind?

22
00:01:54,447 --> 00:01:57,158
-I'm not so…
-They never even talk.

23
00:01:58,201 --> 00:01:59,202
Anyway,

24
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:02,705
you're also applying to the Cheongju
Campus of Gyeongji University, right?

25
00:02:03,748 --> 00:02:04,582
Jae-eun.

26
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:06,376
I'll be done soon, so wait for me.

27
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:11,965
Ki-young.

28
00:02:19,013 --> 00:02:19,848
Jae-eun.

29
00:02:30,608 --> 00:02:31,442
I like you.

30
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:35,697
I like you, Kim Jae-eun.

31
00:02:39,617 --> 00:02:41,578
You knew that, right?

32
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:46,040
I'm sorry.

33
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:52,130
I've never thought of you

34
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:55,675
as anything more than a classmate.

35
00:02:59,304 --> 00:03:00,513
Sorry.

36
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:08,104
Jae-eun.

37
00:03:12,066 --> 00:03:13,902
I mean, Hye-joo.

38
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:16,905
Hi.

39
00:03:22,952 --> 00:03:24,913
THE RIGHT THING TO DO

40
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:35,214
Do you live around here?

41
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:37,884
No.

42
00:03:39,052 --> 00:03:41,304
I asked to meet
in a different neighborhood.

43
00:03:42,096 --> 00:03:43,264
I'm sure you know why.

44
00:03:44,098 --> 00:03:45,058
Right.

45
00:03:45,141 --> 00:03:46,851
Good call.

46
00:03:49,229 --> 00:03:51,189
I know it's late,
but congratulations on your marriage.

47
00:03:51,689 --> 00:03:53,233
You two make a great couple.

48
00:03:54,734 --> 00:03:55,568
Thanks.

49
00:03:58,196 --> 00:04:01,407
I took a peek at Seung-hee's
phone for your number.

50
00:04:02,158 --> 00:04:04,535
Please don't tell her that we met.

51
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:07,205
All right. I won't.

52
00:04:13,836 --> 00:04:14,671
Hye-joo.

53
00:04:17,173 --> 00:04:18,466
About Seung-ho…

54
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:22,887
Could you apologize to them?

55
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:34,107
I thought you were Hye-joo.

56
00:04:34,774 --> 00:04:37,193
What has gotten into you?
You're vacuuming?

57
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:39,696
While you're at it, do the rooms too.

58
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:44,951
-I don't want to.
-You don't…

59
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:46,452
Hey.

60
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:49,455
After all she's done for you,
you can't do this much?

61
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:52,375
She's got it rough these days.

62
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:54,711
-Then you shouldn't stab her in the back.
-What?

63
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:02,051
You can do the master bedroom.

64
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:03,553
I already got Yoon-seo's room.

65
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:07,390
I can't believe that girl.

66
00:05:12,812 --> 00:05:14,689
She said not to go in without permission.

67
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:35,918
AUTOMATIC TRANSFER

68
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,920
100,000 WON TO SINYANG-GU
WOMEN AND YOUTH SHELTER

69
00:05:38,004 --> 00:05:40,340
60,000 WON TO COUNSELING CENTER
FOR SEXUAL VIOLENCE VICTIMS

70
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:41,924
80,000 WON TO SUNFLOWER CHILDREN'S SHELTER

71
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:49,974
200,000 WON TO SUICIDE LOSS SURVIVORS
SUPPORT CENTER

72
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:58,775
I never imagined that
such things happened in Youngsan.

73
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:03,905
Just thinking about what
she's been through breaks my heart.

74
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:11,496
Anyway, I don't think they'll
keep their mouths shut forever.

75
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:15,625
So we need to make the first move
before anything else happens.

76
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:17,251
But I'm worried

77
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:20,088
about Ji Seung-kyu's case.

78
00:06:22,256 --> 00:06:24,967
If they conflate the two cases,
things will get quite messy.

79
00:06:35,394 --> 00:06:37,438
You know what's great about the internet?

80
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,526
You throw them a bone,

81
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:44,737
and they all jump on it at once.

82
00:07:47,175 --> 00:07:48,468
About Seung-ho…

83
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:51,846
Could you apologize to them?

84
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:55,433
I don't know

85
00:07:56,434 --> 00:08:00,271
who is telling the truth
between you and Seung-hee.

86
00:08:01,856 --> 00:08:05,568
I heard the police didn't investigate it
because of Seung-ho's death.

87
00:08:06,652 --> 00:08:07,695
That's why

88
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:11,282
I wanted to ask you in person.

89
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:14,744
I want to know

90
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:16,954
what really happened.

91
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:22,335
But I can already tell

92
00:08:24,128 --> 00:08:24,962
by your face.

93
00:08:26,255 --> 00:08:27,215
You…

94
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:30,092
didn't lie.

95
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:37,433
But Hye-joo.

96
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:40,144
Could you just apologize to them?

97
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:44,982
-But Ki-young--
-You may not have done anything wrong,

98
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:47,568
but you understand the pain
of losing a family member.

99
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:49,529
Don't you?

100
00:08:51,822 --> 00:08:54,742
My mother-in-law is mentally unstable,

101
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:57,203
so Seung-hee always feels restless.

102
00:08:59,413 --> 00:09:03,793
I think the only thing
that could alleviate their situation

103
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:06,837
is your apology.

104
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:10,091
That's why…

105
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:12,969
I'm asking you for a favor.

106
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:16,889
Could you

107
00:09:17,515 --> 00:09:18,724
apologize to them?

108
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:30,861
Hold on tight.

109
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:34,657
You can sit here.

110
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:36,075
Thank you.

111
00:09:43,624 --> 00:09:45,042
Thank you so much.

112
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:46,752
You're not going far, are you?

113
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:48,838
No, I'm getting off
at Jicheong Elementary.

114
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:49,755
I see.

115
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:54,468
Mom, it's like a shower outside.

116
00:09:54,552 --> 00:09:57,096
-My gosh, you're right.
-This stop is…

117
00:09:57,179 --> 00:10:00,933
-It's really pouring down.
-…Korean District Heating Corporation.

118
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:04,145
The next stop is…

119
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:45,519
Goodness, Soo-bin.

120
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,731
Ms. Kim.

121
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:49,690
Hold this.

122
00:10:50,691 --> 00:10:52,109
My goodness.

123
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:53,361
It's okay.

124
00:10:53,444 --> 00:10:55,571
It's pouring down.

125
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:58,407
Why are you outside this late?

126
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:00,242
Let's get you inside.

127
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:02,203
It was raining.

128
00:11:02,286 --> 00:11:03,746
What was that?

129
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:07,416
It was pouring.

130
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:28,312
But if it suddenly
starts pouring at night,

131
00:11:28,938 --> 00:11:31,524
I come by to check at times.

132
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:35,403
Because I'd rather check in person.

133
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:41,033
You said you came to check your studio
when it starts pouring at night.

134
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:44,120
It was pouring down but you weren't home,

135
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:46,539
so I thought you'd be at the studio.

136
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:49,875
I came to make sure just in case,
but the lights were off.

137
00:11:50,459 --> 00:11:53,587
So I went inside
and checked the dehumidifier.

138
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:57,007
-You--
-I know you said

139
00:11:57,091 --> 00:12:00,010
not to go into
your space without permission,

140
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:01,971
but I kept giving you attitude

141
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,432
and hurt your feelings.

142
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:07,726
It felt too awkward to call and ask.

143
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:10,980
So I just went in without telling you.

144
00:12:12,314 --> 00:12:13,482
I'm sorry.

145
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:15,526
It won't happen again.

146
00:12:24,827 --> 00:12:25,786
Don't do this.

147
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:28,873
Don't ever do this again.

148
00:12:32,251 --> 00:12:34,295
Promise me that you won't.

149
00:12:36,547 --> 00:12:37,423
Okay.

150
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:39,300
I won't do it again.

151
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:41,135
Not without asking you--

152
00:12:41,218 --> 00:12:43,220
I don't want anyone to get hurt

153
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:46,307
because of me.

154
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:51,437
Stay safe, Soo-bin.

155
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:52,354
Both you…

156
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:54,482
and your baby, okay?

157
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:01,238
The fetus's heart has stopped.

158
00:13:03,073 --> 00:13:04,492
It's a miscarriage.

159
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:11,749
So don't ever get rained on because of me.

160
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:12,958
Okay?

161
00:14:09,431 --> 00:14:12,017
An amendment to
the Criminal Act that allows

162
00:14:12,101 --> 00:14:15,145
the investigation to continue
even after the sex crime suspect dies

163
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:17,731
and becomes unable to be prosecuted?

164
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:23,028
You realize there are
some juridical issues there, right?

165
00:14:23,112 --> 00:14:24,113
Yes.

166
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:28,409
Continuing an investigation
without anyone there to punish

167
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:31,745
contradicts the foundation
of the criminal justice system.

168
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:35,457
But the juridical aspect of the matter

169
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:38,377
will only be understood by people
like us who have studied law.

170
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:40,421
Public sentiment is a different story.

171
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:46,927
Public sentiment has
nothing to do with legislation.

172
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:49,221
But I'm sure you're aware of that.

173
00:14:51,098 --> 00:14:53,392
During my time as a judge,

174
00:14:53,475 --> 00:14:56,979
I saw many sexual violence victims
experience secondary victimization

175
00:14:57,062 --> 00:14:59,064
after the assailants

176
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:00,858
took their own lives.

177
00:15:02,234 --> 00:15:04,278
However, the law is the law.

178
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:06,405
And it won't just be difficult

179
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:09,033
for this amendment to pass.

180
00:15:09,116 --> 00:15:10,701
It will be impossible.

181
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:15,998
Even if you manage to win over the public,

182
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,543
all there's left will be controversy.

183
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,587
I welcome controversy.

184
00:15:22,379 --> 00:15:24,882
That controversy will
arouse people's interest

185
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:27,593
and make what's impossible, possible.

186
00:15:29,219 --> 00:15:32,348
When you suggested that I run
as a list member eight years ago,

187
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:34,350
you said that I couldn't
work alone in politics

188
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:36,518
and that I'll need
the public and the party's support.

189
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:40,064
I'll form the public opinion.

190
00:15:40,147 --> 00:15:43,317
I'm asking you to lead the party
as the chairwoman

191
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,027
in supporting this amendment.

192
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,599
Things must have been hectic for you

193
00:16:16,183 --> 00:16:17,393
with Ji-hoon's incident.

194
00:16:19,186 --> 00:16:21,188
It took a bigger toll on Hye-joo.

195
00:16:21,730 --> 00:16:22,731
But thankfully,

196
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:25,609
she seems to be doing better.

197
00:16:31,865 --> 00:16:35,452
You know, you haven't changed a bit

198
00:16:35,536 --> 00:16:37,413
since the first time we met.

199
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:48,590
I'll do my best

200
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:50,884
alongside Attorney Nam Joong-do.

201
00:16:58,350 --> 00:17:01,103
MAN ATTEMPTS SUICIDE
AFTER KILLING HIS FAMILY

202
00:17:01,186 --> 00:17:02,229
PUNISH FILICIDE SEVERELY

203
00:17:02,312 --> 00:17:04,523
I'll never forget how hard you tried

204
00:17:04,606 --> 00:17:08,110
to get my story out
after I filed the constitutional appeal.

205
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:10,779
Thank you so much for that.

206
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:12,406
Don't mention it.

207
00:17:12,489 --> 00:17:14,992
Plus, your appeal was
dismissed in the end.

208
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:18,912
We couldn't change anything. I'm sorry.

209
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:20,873
Don't say that.

210
00:17:20,956 --> 00:17:24,251
I knew it was an uphill battle.

211
00:17:28,255 --> 00:17:31,133
But as I fought through it,

212
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:33,510
I realized that I had
a lot of people on my side

213
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:35,012
and it helped me go on.

214
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:44,104
Do you regret quitting
your job as a reporter

215
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:45,439
to be in the National Assembly?

216
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,610
I do.

217
00:17:50,944 --> 00:17:52,863
That was a permanent position,

218
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:54,865
but my current position is temporary.

219
00:17:55,824 --> 00:17:58,869
Assemblyman Nam can fire me
at a moment's notice.

220
00:18:01,955 --> 00:18:04,958
If you get fired,
I'll give you a job here.

221
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:06,752
Okay, well…

222
00:18:07,836 --> 00:18:09,338
I'll give it some thought.

223
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:14,635
I became a reporter…

224
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:17,805
wanting to change this world.

225
00:18:18,847 --> 00:18:21,850
Then I met Assemblyman Nam
during my rookie days.

226
00:18:22,684 --> 00:18:23,811
And then…

227
00:18:24,603 --> 00:18:27,523
I got to know him better
through Chae-eun's case.

228
00:18:28,899 --> 00:18:32,820
I began to think that
I could bet my life on him.

229
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:38,200
So when he asked me
to join him in the Assembly

230
00:18:38,283 --> 00:18:39,910
seven and a half years ago,

231
00:18:41,161 --> 00:18:42,538
I quit without hesitation.

232
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:49,378
So I hope the general election goes well

233
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:52,714
and we'll go further.

234
00:19:03,225 --> 00:19:04,226
You know…

235
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:08,480
-Mr. Jang.
-Betting my life on him

236
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:11,275
was the best option I had,

237
00:19:14,361 --> 00:19:16,572
and I will make it
the best decision of my life.

238
00:19:25,497 --> 00:19:26,456
Anyway,

239
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:29,501
you had something to tell me today.

240
00:19:32,212 --> 00:19:33,172
What was it?

241
00:19:35,132 --> 00:19:36,258
Please tell me.

242
00:19:42,222 --> 00:19:43,557
Is it about Assemblyman Nam?

243
00:19:47,269 --> 00:19:48,145
No.

244
00:19:50,606 --> 00:19:52,441
It wasn't anything important.

245
00:19:57,487 --> 00:19:58,405
Okay.

246
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:08,290
Come in.

247
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:17,799
Come in and put on the slippers.

248
00:20:19,635 --> 00:20:21,386
This is our only bathtub.

249
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:25,015
My husband will be home late,
so don't worry about him.

250
00:20:25,098 --> 00:20:26,391
Warm yourself up.

251
00:20:26,975 --> 00:20:28,852
Make yourself at home and take your time.

252
00:20:55,128 --> 00:20:55,963
Yoon-seo.

253
00:21:01,593 --> 00:21:02,844
You haven't gone to sleep.

254
00:21:02,928 --> 00:21:04,596
No, but I'm going to bed soon.

255
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,514
What's up?

256
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:12,771
What are you doing, Mom?

257
00:21:12,854 --> 00:21:16,316
When did my little girl grow up so much?

258
00:21:21,655 --> 00:21:24,241
-Were you doing homework?
-Yes.

259
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:25,659
Mom.

260
00:21:25,742 --> 00:21:27,411
Have you heard of the Trolley Dilemma?

261
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:30,414
-The Trolley Dilemma?
-Yes.

262
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:32,499
Here's the thing.

263
00:21:33,166 --> 00:21:34,793
This is the trolley.

264
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:38,463
And the brakes are broken,

265
00:21:38,547 --> 00:21:39,923
so if it keeps going,

266
00:21:40,007 --> 00:21:41,758
-it'll kill five people.
-Okay.

267
00:21:41,842 --> 00:21:45,095
But if you switch the track,

268
00:21:45,178 --> 00:21:47,055
it'll change its direction
and only kill one.

