00:40:21,669 --> 00:40:23,712
This medication is only for nighttime.

543
00:40:24,255 --> 00:40:25,423
Did you take these today?

544
00:40:25,506 --> 00:40:27,383
The doctor said it's only for nights.

545
00:40:27,466 --> 00:40:29,677
I didn't take any today.

546
00:40:31,929 --> 00:40:33,222
"Today"?

547
00:40:33,305 --> 00:40:34,932
So you've been
taking these during the day?

548
00:40:35,015 --> 00:40:37,351
-Mom.
-Stop yelling!

549
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:38,727
Goodness.

550
00:40:38,811 --> 00:40:42,106
If you're so worried,
do something about it.

551
00:40:43,023 --> 00:40:45,609
You abandoned your sick mom
and went abroad,

552
00:40:45,693 --> 00:40:47,403
and now you're pretending to be worried?

553
00:40:47,486 --> 00:40:49,572
-Mom.
-I don't want to hear it. Get out.

554
00:41:04,837 --> 00:41:06,630
KO SEONG-CHANG (YOUNGSAN SCHOOLMATE)

555
00:41:06,714 --> 00:41:10,384
Sorry. My sister-in-law says
she can't disclose personal information.

556
00:41:45,753 --> 00:41:47,588
I'm sorry, but please excuse me.

557
00:41:47,671 --> 00:41:48,923
I'm not very hungry.

558
00:41:49,423 --> 00:41:50,341
Okay.

559
00:41:52,468 --> 00:41:54,512
Hye-joo, are you okay? Are you hurt?

560
00:41:54,595 --> 00:41:55,429
Give me the rag.

561
00:41:55,513 --> 00:41:56,597
Stand still. You'll get hurt.

562
00:41:56,680 --> 00:41:58,557
-It's okay, I got it.
-Give it to me.

563
00:42:03,229 --> 00:42:04,063
What's wrong?

564
00:42:05,022 --> 00:42:06,065
Is something going on?

565
00:42:11,570 --> 00:42:12,404
Yeo-jin.

566
00:42:15,574 --> 00:42:17,493
Back when I lived in Youngsan,

567
00:42:19,411 --> 00:42:21,747
my friend's brother died.

568
00:42:24,750 --> 00:42:27,920
I was molested by him,
so I went to the police.

569
00:42:30,089 --> 00:42:31,048
And that night,

570
00:42:34,510 --> 00:42:35,719
he killed himself.

571
00:42:49,692 --> 00:42:50,776
Yeo-jin.

572
00:42:52,903 --> 00:42:56,115
I never imagined
that he would end up like that.

573
00:42:57,157 --> 00:42:58,117
It's okay.

574
00:42:59,285 --> 00:43:00,536
You don't have to say anything.

575
00:43:01,453 --> 00:43:03,163
You don't have to say anything, Hye-joo.

576
00:43:04,456 --> 00:43:05,791
Goodness.

577
00:43:07,167 --> 00:43:08,919
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

578
00:43:10,963 --> 00:43:12,756
How could you keep this bottled up

579
00:43:13,716 --> 00:43:15,759
without telling anyone for so long?

580
00:43:19,471 --> 00:43:21,223
It must have been so tough.

581
00:43:31,483 --> 00:43:33,861
In the end, nothing was resolved.

582
00:43:36,155 --> 00:43:37,323
Joong-do said

583
00:43:37,948 --> 00:43:39,867
that he'd take care of everything

584
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:41,827
and that I shouldn't do anything.

585
00:43:42,786 --> 00:43:43,787
But…

586
00:43:45,289 --> 00:43:51,712
I think it might be best for everyone
if I apologized to his mother.

587
00:43:52,713 --> 00:43:53,922
No, Hye-joo.

588
00:43:54,506 --> 00:43:55,966
Your husband is a public figure.

589
00:43:56,675 --> 00:44:00,304
If you apologize,
they'll use that to blackmail you again.

590
00:44:01,138 --> 00:44:02,139
Still…

591
00:44:03,349 --> 00:44:05,100
His mother and my friend

592
00:44:05,851 --> 00:44:07,853
lost a son and a brother.

593
00:44:10,898 --> 00:44:14,485
After losing Ji-hoon,
I can understand their pain,

594
00:44:15,361 --> 00:44:17,780
and it just torments me even more.

595
00:44:21,617 --> 00:44:22,618
I see.

596
00:44:25,954 --> 00:44:27,748
I know how it feels to lose your child.

597
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:29,500
I understand.

598
00:44:31,835 --> 00:44:32,836
But Hye-joo.

599
00:44:33,837 --> 00:44:35,214
You shouldn't apologize.

600
00:44:36,173 --> 00:44:38,926
You don't apologize
for something like this.

601
00:44:39,009 --> 00:44:41,553
You show remorse
for what happened. That's all.

602
00:44:44,348 --> 00:44:45,974
It was an accident.

603
00:44:46,892 --> 00:44:48,185
It wasn't your fault.

604
00:44:57,277 --> 00:44:59,363
It's always hard for those
who are left behind.

605
00:45:01,323 --> 00:45:04,243
I heard the mill lady tried
to follow her granddaughter.

606
00:45:05,327 --> 00:45:08,288
She was in shock about
her granddaughter's video getting leaked.

607
00:45:10,749 --> 00:45:13,085
Who told you that?

608
00:45:14,253 --> 00:45:15,671
What?

609
00:45:15,754 --> 00:45:17,381
About the mill lady.

610
00:45:18,090 --> 00:45:20,592
Joong-do mentioned it on TV
this afternoon.

611
00:45:23,011 --> 00:45:24,138
On TV?

612
00:45:24,221 --> 00:45:25,514
GRANDMOTHER ATTEMPTS SUICIDE
AFTER VIDEO LEAK

613
00:45:25,597 --> 00:45:26,807
TODAY'S ISSUE 24

614
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:30,936
REPORTER PARK YEONG-SU INTERVIEWS
ASSEMBLYMAN NAM JOONG-DO

615
00:45:33,689 --> 00:45:35,315
COMMENTS

616
00:45:35,399 --> 00:45:36,900
HE'S A BASTARD EVEN AFTER DYING

617
00:45:36,984 --> 00:45:38,610
ONCE AN ASSHOLE, ALWAYS AN ASSHOLE

618
00:45:38,694 --> 00:45:39,945
JOONG-DO SERVING UP JUSTICE AGAIN

619
00:45:43,407 --> 00:45:46,410
THIS IS HIS PARENTS' RESTAURANT

620
00:45:51,915 --> 00:45:54,418
SEUNG-KYU'S DINING TABLE

621
00:46:08,348 --> 00:46:10,142
DID THEY NOT KNOW THEIR SON
WAS A PIECE OF SHIT?

622
00:46:10,225 --> 00:46:11,101
I HOPE THEY ALL DIE

623
00:46:11,185 --> 00:46:12,895
I'M SUSPICIOUS OF THE GRANDDAUGHTER TOO

624
00:46:18,358 --> 00:46:19,193
Hey.

625
00:46:19,943 --> 00:46:22,029
Why are you still up? It's late.

626
00:46:24,781 --> 00:46:26,575
Why won't you say anything?
You're scaring me.

627
00:46:26,658 --> 00:46:27,951
Did I do something wrong?

628
00:46:29,453 --> 00:46:31,121
-Honey.
-Yes?

629
00:46:33,540 --> 00:46:37,085
About your appearance
on TV this afternoon…

630
00:46:37,669 --> 00:46:39,004
So you saw that?

631
00:46:39,087 --> 00:46:40,464
Yes.

632
00:46:41,507 --> 00:46:43,050
Did you have to mention

633
00:46:44,593 --> 00:46:46,512
the mill lady on TV?

634
00:46:47,137 --> 00:46:48,347
What do you mean?

635
00:46:49,556 --> 00:46:50,432
Look at this.

636
00:46:51,475 --> 00:46:53,727
Everyone is cursing out
the med student's parents.

637
00:46:58,440 --> 00:46:59,441
So what about it?

638
00:47:01,777 --> 00:47:05,822
When the suicide attempt
of his mother made the news,

639
00:47:05,906 --> 00:47:07,741
the family got really harsh comments.

640
00:47:07,824 --> 00:47:10,786
And now that you mentioned
the mill lady on TV today,

641
00:47:10,869 --> 00:47:12,120
it's happening again.

642
00:47:13,038 --> 00:47:16,500
That med student
did commit a serious crime,

643
00:47:16,583 --> 00:47:20,337
but his mother tried to kill herself
after seeing comments against her son.

644
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:22,673
With another flood
of all these hateful comments…

645
00:47:23,924 --> 00:47:25,842
I'm really worried, honey.

646
00:47:26,927 --> 00:47:29,805
I did it for the mill lady
and her granddaughter.

647
00:47:30,389 --> 00:47:33,225
Some people are criticizing her
and her granddaughter too.

648
00:47:33,308 --> 00:47:36,812
They're saying she was after money
and that this is a show for settlement.

649
00:47:36,895 --> 00:47:38,021
If she finds out…

650
00:47:38,105 --> 00:47:39,273
Don't worry about that.

651
00:47:39,856 --> 00:47:41,108
She already knows.

652
00:47:41,900 --> 00:47:43,110
How does she know?

653
00:47:43,193 --> 00:47:46,113
I went to the hospital
to get permission to share her story,

654
00:47:46,613 --> 00:47:48,782
and I told her what to expect.

655
00:47:51,952 --> 00:47:55,330
You can make use of me
as much as you like.

656
00:47:55,414 --> 00:47:57,457
I don't care what people say about me

657
00:47:58,041 --> 00:48:01,003
as long as the world knows
about Sol's misfortune.

658
00:48:11,722 --> 00:48:15,350
But I keep worrying about
the med student's parents

659
00:48:15,434 --> 00:48:17,519
whenever I hear her granddaughter come up.

660
00:48:17,603 --> 00:48:19,438
Why do you empathize with the assailant?

661
00:48:20,022 --> 00:48:22,065
I'm not empathizing!

662
00:48:22,149 --> 00:48:24,276
What would you call this then?

663
00:48:24,359 --> 00:48:25,611
No, I'm just…

664
00:48:34,369 --> 00:48:35,621
Fine, I am empathizing.

665
00:48:35,704 --> 00:48:37,998
But not with the assailant.
With his mother.

666
00:48:38,749 --> 00:48:41,585
That med student is obviously a criminal,

667
00:48:42,461 --> 00:48:43,712
but what about his family?

668
00:48:44,838 --> 00:48:47,341
They're still here living in pain.

669
00:48:47,424 --> 00:48:50,552
If something else bad happens,
how will the rest of them live?

670
00:48:50,636 --> 00:48:52,179
-Hye-joo.
-Honey.

671
00:48:53,555 --> 00:48:57,517
I'm so scared that another
tragedy might take place.

672
00:49:00,103 --> 00:49:04,399
So I wish you'd stop using the media

673
00:49:04,983 --> 00:49:07,944
to make a bigger issue out of this.

674
00:49:08,904 --> 00:49:09,905
Honey.

675
00:49:10,906 --> 00:49:11,990
Stop it.

676
00:49:13,033 --> 00:49:14,326
Please stop this.

677
00:49:15,410 --> 00:49:16,870
I'm begging you.

678
00:49:18,789 --> 00:49:19,623
I'm sorry.

679
00:49:20,624 --> 00:49:22,000
But this will only get bigger.

680
00:49:22,584 --> 00:49:24,127
Until the entire country knows.

681
00:49:25,128 --> 00:49:25,962
Honey.

682
00:49:26,922 --> 00:49:28,632
I'm going to propose an amendment

683
00:49:29,716 --> 00:49:33,428
that allows investigations to continue
even after a sex criminal dies.

684
00:49:34,388 --> 00:49:36,723
I'll need more of those
hate comments in the future.

685
00:49:37,516 --> 00:49:40,435
That's the public sentiment
that will help this amendment pass.

686
00:49:42,354 --> 00:49:46,233
I'm trying to prevent more pain
caused by the suicide of assailants.

687
00:49:46,817 --> 00:49:49,277
Don't you want that too?

688
00:49:53,865 --> 00:49:55,534
If the law had been different,

689
00:49:55,617 --> 00:49:59,162
you and that family wouldn't have
had to live in pain for 20 years.

690
00:50:06,169 --> 00:50:07,754
So please support me in my plan.

691
00:50:09,506 --> 00:50:11,675
Your support is
the most important thing to me.

692
00:50:13,468 --> 00:50:15,971
I need the support of my beloved wife.

693
00:50:29,609 --> 00:50:30,736
You should go to sleep.

694
00:50:31,820 --> 00:50:33,071
We'll talk again later.

695
00:50:40,454 --> 00:50:42,372
Collateral damage is inevitable

696
00:50:43,206 --> 00:50:45,000
for the greater good.

697
00:51:38,762 --> 00:51:39,805
Ms. Kim.

698
00:51:40,430 --> 00:51:41,515
Hey, you're up.

699
00:51:42,432 --> 00:51:44,017
Are you feeling okay?

700
00:51:44,643 --> 00:51:45,477
Yes.

701
00:51:46,228 --> 00:51:48,438
Go have breakfast.
You skipped dinner last night.

702
00:51:50,023 --> 00:51:52,651
You don't have to
prepare meals for me anymore.

703
00:51:54,277 --> 00:51:55,320
Okay.

704
00:51:55,403 --> 00:51:57,447
But it was Yeo-jin today.

705
00:51:57,531 --> 00:51:59,115
You should thank her later.

706
00:51:59,699 --> 00:52:00,951
Okay.

707
00:52:01,535 --> 00:52:02,577
Bye, then.

708
00:52:04,371 --> 00:52:05,580
Wait, Ms. Kim.

709
00:52:06,206 --> 00:52:07,415
Yes? What is it?

710
00:52:11,086 --> 00:52:12,045
It's nothing.

711
00:52:13,839 --> 00:52:15,173
Go ahead and eat.

712
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:16,484
Ms. Kim Soo-bin.

713
00:53:20,363 --> 00:53:21,531
So…

714
00:53:22,699 --> 00:53:24,075
you can't tell Ms. Kim

715
00:53:24,701 --> 00:53:26,328
about this.

716
00:53:27,662 --> 00:53:28,914
Okay?

717
00:54:20,090 --> 00:54:21,633
Today, not tomorrow?

718
00:54:27,263 --> 00:54:29,849
In that case, can you come around 3 p.m.?

719
00:54:29,933 --> 00:54:31,559
I'm finishing up right now.

720
00:54:33,895 --> 00:54:35,230
Okay, thank you.

721
00:54:39,526 --> 00:54:42,195
YOUR PACKAGE FROM PRINT PHOTO
HAS BEEN DELIVERED

722
00:55:23,361 --> 00:55:25,238
JI-HOON'S MATERNAL GRANDMOTHER

723
00:55:25,321 --> 00:55:28,116
How come I never thought
of sending her photos?

724
00:55:41,337 --> 00:55:43,089
Soo-bin, I'm stopping by for a moment.

725
00:55:45,175 --> 00:55:46,051
Is she asleep?

726
00:55:54,642 --> 00:55:56,770
I remember buying some large envelopes.

727
00:55:57,645 --> 00:55:58,897
Right, the envelope.

728
00:55:59,689 --> 00:56:01,149
In a drawer in the study.

729
00:56:02,025 --> 00:56:02,984
Right.

730
00:56:31,721 --> 00:56:33,139
That's where the ink pad was.

731
00:56:38,770 --> 00:56:39,771
Not here.

732
00:56:45,401 --> 00:56:46,653
ASSEMBLYMAN NAM JOONG-DO

733
00:56:48,321 --> 00:56:49,948
ASSEMBLYMAN NAM JOONG-DO

734
00:57:31,823 --> 00:57:33,074
The police

735
00:57:33,158 --> 00:57:35,910
couldn't find the phone
Ji-hoon had been using.

736
00:57:57,682 --> 00:58:03,771
SOO-BIN

737
00:58:11,112 --> 00:58:13,281
Don't ever say you want to break up.

738
00:58:13,364 --> 00:58:14,908
Do you have a death wish?

739
00:58:24,792 --> 00:58:26,085
Ji-hoon died…

740
00:58:30,632 --> 00:58:32,008
because of that kid.

741
00:58:45,146 --> 00:58:46,314
I'm going to kill myself.

742
00:58:46,397 --> 00:58:48,274
I'M GOING TO KILL MYSELF

743
00:59:46,332 --> 00:59:49,294
TROLLEY

744
00:59:49,377 --> 00:59:51,754
If you were going to hide it,
you should have been more thorough.

745
00:59:51,838 --> 00:59:52,839
It was just a mistake.

746
00:59:52,922 --> 00:59:55,258
Let's work together as victims
and make something happen.

747
00:59:55,341 --> 00:59:57,427
Arrange a meeting with Nam Joong-do.

748
00:59:57,510 --> 00:59:59,887
How could you betray me like this?

749
00:59:59,971 --> 01:00:00,972
How did you miss this?

750
01:00:01,055 --> 01:00:02,765
Nothing is going as planned!

751
01:00:02,849 --> 01:00:04,017
Can you believe her?

752
01:00:04,100 --> 01:00:05,310
Yeo-jin, please keep it a secret.

753
01:00:05,393 --> 01:00:07,270
I was being as generous
as I possibly could.

754
01:00:07,353 --> 01:00:09,522
Everything a politician does
sends out a message.

755
01:00:09,606 --> 01:00:11,524
You're at fault no matter what.

